1. A x (B ∪ {5})
First, we find the union of B and {5}: B ∪ {5} = {3, 4, 5}
Now, we find the Cartesian product of A and (B ∪ {5}):
A x (B ∪ {5}) = {(1,3), (1,4), (1,5), (2,3), (2,4), (2,5)}

2. (A x B) ∪ (A x {5})
First, we find the Cartesian products A x B and A x {5}:
A x B = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}
A x {5} = {(1,5), (2,5)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:
(A x B) ∪ (A x {5}) = {(1,3), (1,4), (1,5), (2,3), (2,4), (2,5)}

As we can see, both expressions result in the same set: {(1,3), (1,4), (1,5), (2,3), (2,4), (2,5)}.
